decision_conditions:
Condition : 3 - No development shall commence until a Construction and Environmental Management Plan (CEMP) has been submitted to and been approved in writing by the local planning authority. The CEMP shall include measures to mitigate the construction effects in accordance with the measures outlined in the Preliminary Ecological Appraisal (Deepdene Ecology, May 2024) and the following details (although not limited to): 
a)	whilst works should take place outside of the nesting season (February - September inclusive), if works are unavoidable during this period, then a site walk over no more than 24 hours prior to works commencing is required by a named CIEEM accredited ecologist with experience of working in London to check for any nesting birds in the exiting buildings and structures to be demolished. In the event that a nest is found, an appropriate exclusion zone should be implemented around it until the young have fully fledged (Wildlife and Countryside Act 1981 (as amended)). 
b)	details of measures to be taken to ensure that retained and adjacent habitats, in particular Garratt Park and the River Wandle SINC, will not be used for storage or impacted negatively by the works (including, but not limited to vehicle movement, runoff, storage, lighting, dust, litter, noise etc. and as outlined in the PEA (Deepdene Ecology, May 2024);
c)	details of toolbox talks for all workers onsite, which should cover badgers, hedgehogs, bats, the River Wandle SINC and other adjacent habitats;
d)	if lighting is necessary, details of a construction lighting plan (including the locations of light fittings, the types of light fittings and the lux spill levels) outlining how lighting will be prevented from negatively impacting any protected and priority species during construction, in particular commuting bats, and adjacent habitats, in particular the River Wandle SINC where there must be no light spill. 
e)	details of measures to prevent mammal, amphibian or reptile entrapment or harm on site,
